@HeathieJ 

Uzo ADUBA is not a writer; she's the actress who played Suzanne "Crazy Eyes" Warren in Orange is the New Black.

Her last name has appeared four times, and her first name nine times, with one additional appearance for her full name.  With her vowel-laden name, she will appear quite frequently as long as she remains active.

@Henry Su 

The answer history for ERM is interesting: 10 appearances in the pre-Shortz era, always clued as a fur (abbr.), a long hiatus (1977–2016), and then six appearances clued more or less as it was today. 

That was the last word I put in the grid. Somehow, I managed to type an O for the R of ODOR.

@Steve L 

Yes, ERM was an abbreviation for “ermine.” Most of the clues had some modifier for “fur” such as “royal” or “luxurious.” And you’re right, it’s a horrible abbreviation that probably was never used outside a crossword puzzle. 

Speaking of which — I don’t know that I have ever heard anyone use ERM in conversation.

